    <note>Shu(2) Zhao [17045] This man was the earliest Song Mingzhou, Fenghua county Shu(2) jinshi. Although Dan [1483], a 1065 jinshi, is identified as a Ciqi county jinshi, his descendant. Lie [10285], is listed as a Fenghua jinshi in Zhejiang TZ, 125.34b. I am assuming that Zhao was a lineage (third) uncle of Bian [17049], who has the same generational name as Lin(2) [17438], Yong [17048] and Dan and that Bian and Dan's lineages represent two branches of a common root lineage, perhaps deriving from the Dongyang county Shu(2) jinshi listed for Tang. Zhejiang TZ, 123.29a; Fenghua xianzhi, 19.966.</note>
